item.title: Steve King Demands Conditions For Disaster Aid
item.description: Steve King: Hurricane Sandy Aid Must Have Strings To Avoid Waste On 'Gucci Bags' http://t.co/2MOmEbqe #Huffington #News
item.content:encoded: Steve King: Hurricane Sandy Aid Must Have Strings To Avoid Waste On 'Gucci Bags' http://t.co/2MOmEbqe #Huffington #News WASHINGTON -- Rep. Steve King (R-Iowa) said on Tuesday that federal aid for people impacted by Hurricane Sandy should be approved only with a specific spending plan in place so funds are not used for "Gucci bags and massage parlors," like after Hurricane Katrina. "I want to get them the resources that are necessary to lift them out of this water and the sand and the ashes and the death that's over there in the East Coast and especially in the Northeast," King said during a Tuesday evening debate in Mason City, Iowa.
